abstract: A show of a hundred 17th-century objects, such as cases full of Dutch gold jewelry, Massachusetts colonial coins, Indonesian silver bowls and Japanese lacquered plates at the Bard Graduate Center.
snippet: A show of a hundred 17th-century objects, such as cases full of Dutch gold jewelry, Massachusetts colonial coins, Indonesian silver bowls and Japanese lacquered plates at the Bard Graduate Center.
lead_paragraph: Scholars are not sure what Margrieta van Varick looked like, or even how she spelled her name, even though she ran a successful furnishings import business in Dutch New York. In her meager surviving paperwork from the 1690s the name variants include Margrita, Grietje and Magret. What is known is exactly how many ebony-framed mirrors, silver-headed walking sticks, muslin curtains and porcelain cups she wanted her four young children to inherit as she lay dying at her Flatbush home in 1695, age 46.

abstract: Since nonprofit groups do not pay income taxes, they would not benefit from a tax credit for small businesses that provide health insurance to employees.
snippet: Since nonprofit groups do not pay income taxes, they would not benefit from a tax credit for small businesses that provide health insurance to employees.
lead_paragraph: Nonprofit organizations say they are upset that Congress and the Obama administration have not addressed their rising health care costs in the various health care proposals being floated on Capitol Hill.

abstract: The 2009-10 theater season in New Jersey offers proof that managers are working to keep the economy from affecting what appears on stage.
snippet: The 2009-10 theater season in New Jersey offers proof that managers are working to keep the economy from affecting what appears on stage.
lead_paragraph: WHETHER drama, comedy or musical, most New Jersey theater productions for the 2009-10 season will contain an element of magic. Not the rabbit-out-of-a-hat kind, but the sort of alchemy in which theater management works to keep tough financial times from affecting what appears on stage.
